					<description><![CDATA[<p>See the data behind Google's rising search feature, AI Overviews, including how AIOs are impacting CTR and user experience. </p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-overviews-statistics">Google AI Overviews: 34 Stats &#038; Facts You Can&#8217;t Scroll Past</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In 2024, Google launched AI Overviews (AIOs), a search engine results page (SERP) feature that uses AI to generate answers to queries. AI Overviews allow users to get an answer to their question directly at the top of the SERP rather than clicking off to an actual search result link.</p>
<p>AI Overviews have caused quite a stir, with many users finding inaccuracies in the AI-generated responses and many businesses seeing traffic from Google decline. Yet, despite this, Google reports AI Overviews are widely used.</p>
<p>So, just how often are AIOs showing up in results, how do users actually feel about AIOs, and how are they really impacting site traffic?</p>
<p>I‚Äôve got answers (not sourced from AI) to all that and more in this breakdown of Google AI Overviews statistics complete with a handy infographic to help you stay informed and one step ahead of AI in the search space.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#google-ai-overviews-statistics-top-picks">AI Overviews statistics and facts: Our top picks</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ai-overviews-statistics-frequency">How often are AI Overviews showing up?</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ai-overviews-statistics-usage">How are people using AIOs?</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ai-overviews-statistics-click-impact">Do Google AI Overviews reduce clicks from the SERP?</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ai-overviews-statistics-more-stats">Even more AIO stats and fun facts</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ai-overviews-statistics-infographic">Google AIO stats infographic</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="google-ai-overviews-statistics-top-picks"></div>
<h2>Google AI Overviews statistics and facts: Our top picks</h2>
<p>Here are the most crucial data points surrounding <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-overviews-breaking-search" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google AI Overviews</a> that you won‚Äôt want to miss.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Could<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/common-website-mistakes?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_WebsiteMistakes_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> these common website mistakes</a> stop your business from showing up in AIOs?</strong> Find out for free here!</p>
<h3>1. About <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-links-to-itself-43-of-ai-overviews-point-back-to-google/546574/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">43%</a> of AIOs link back to results from Google itself.</h3>
<p>Google appears as a source in nearly 44% of all AI-generated Overview answers.</p>
<h3>2. Nearly <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-keywords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">100%</a> of keywords that trigger AI Overviews are of informational intent.</h3>
<p>AI Overviews only have a 10% chance of showing for commercial or transactional keywords.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/keyword-search-intent-1-png.avif" alt="different types of keyword intents" width="936" height="600" class="wp-image-90734 size-full aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/keyword-search-intent-1-png.avif 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/keyword-search-intent-1-300x192.avif 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/keyword-search-intent-1-768x492.avif 768w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/keyword-search-intent-1-480x308.avif 480w" sizes="(max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px" /></p>
<h3>3. About <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-keywords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">81%</a> of AIO SERPs also include a ‚ÄúPeople Also Ask‚Äù section.</h3>
<p>With both AIOs and PAA taking up valuable SERP space, it‚Äôs more important than ever for you to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/06/how-to-rank-higher-on-google" target="_blank" rel="noopener">prioritize your Google rank</a> in terms of both SEO and PPC.</p>
<h3>4. <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-keywords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">40%</a> of sources shown in AIOs would rank in spots 11-20 on the SERP, rather than the top 10.</h3>
<p>With nearly half of AIO sources having a ranking lower than the top 10, this indicates that higher-ranking content won‚Äôt necessarily have a chance to pop up in an AIO.</p>
<h3>5. The top 50 domains on Google get nearly <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/insights-from-56-million-ai-overviews/">30%</a> of all AIO mentions.</h3>
<p>Clearly, AIOs favor high-powered, high-authority sites‚Äîmaking it more difficult for smaller sites to make their way into AI-generated results and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/llm-tracking">mentions</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-ranking-content.webp" alt="google ai overviews - top sources" width="500" height="800" class="aligncenter wp-image-92056 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-ranking-content.webp 500w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-ranking-content-480x768.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 500px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="google-ai-overviews-statistics-frequency"></div>
<h2>How often are AI Overviews showing?</h2>
<p>So, how often can you <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-overviews" target="_blank" rel="noopener">expect an AIO to pop up</a> on the same SERPs your business lands on? Let‚Äôs see what the data says.</p>
<h3>6. AIOs show for almost <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/insights-from-56-million-ai-overviews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">55%</a> of Google searches.</h3>
<p>Odds are,<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-overviews-impact-on-seo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> your business is showing up alongside AI Overviews</a>. Be sure to optimize your SEO and PPC strategies with that in mind.</p>
<h3>7. Since March 2025, AI Overviews have grown by <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-growth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">115%</a>.</h3>
<p>This comes after the <a href="https://status.search.google.com/incidents/zpmwuSwifjDjfrVdaZUx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">March core update</a> from Google.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-how-often-they-show.webp" alt="google ai overviews - ai overview frequency chart" width="495" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92048 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-how-often-they-show.webp 495w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-how-often-they-show-480x582.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 495px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>8. AI Overviews keyword share has <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-growth/">doubled</a> since March 2025.</h3>
<p>More and more keywords are able to trigger AIOs. Try <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/08/09/easy-keyword-research-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">using keyword tools</a> to get ideas for keywords related to your business that are most likely to have an AIO in their results. From there, you can optimize for those keywords or try to avoid them, depending on your strategy.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f50d.png" alt="üîç" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Keyword Tool</a> can help you tailor your SEO strategy with AIOs in mind!</strong></p>
<h3>9. AIOs show up <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/insights-from-56-million-ai-overviews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">less than normal</a> for local queries.</h3>
<p>AIOs only show on about 7% of all local queries. This aligns with other trends that have found <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/local-seo-in-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local SEO</a> to be relatively safe from AI and other algorithm updates.</p>
<h3>10. The longer the search query, the more likely it is to get an AIO.</h3>
<p>AIOs show up <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/insights-from-56-million-ai-overviews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">less</a> in shorter search queries and more in longer search queries. In fact, a query with eight words or more is <a href="https://searchengineland.com/google-ai-overviews-search-clicks-fell-report-455498" target="_blank" rel="noopener">7x</a> more likely to get an AI Overview in its results.</p>
<div id="google-ai-overviews-statistics-usage"></div>
<h2>How are people using AIOs?</h2>
<p>If you‚Äôre wondering how much attention your customers are paying to AIOs, you‚Äôre not alone. Here‚Äôs what we know so far in terms of consumer sentiment around AIOs, along with the impact AIOs have on user experience.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong>Ready to incorporate AI in your business&#8217;s search strategy?</strong> Download our free guide to<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/ai-advertising?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_AIAdvertising_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> powerful ways to use AI in Google and Facebook Ads</a>!</p>
<h3>11. <a href="https://www.growth-memo.com/p/the-first-ever-ux-study-of-googles" target="_blank" rel="noopener">7 in 10</a> searchers only read the first few lines of an AIO.</h3>
<p>The majority of Google users aren‚Äôt looking past the first third of an AIO result. In other words, they‚Äôre only reading about 30% of an AIO‚Äôs information.</p>
<h3>12. <a href="https://www.growth-memo.com/p/the-first-ever-ux-study-of-googles" target="_blank" rel="noopener">88%</a> of users click ‚Äúshow more‚Äù to expand truncated AIOs‚Äîeven if they don‚Äôt read it.</h3>
<p>This might seem contradictory, but while users may not always be reading AIOs in their entirety, many are still expanding them to, at least, see the whole result before scanning past.</p>
<h3>13. <a href="https://searchengineland.com/search-engine-traffic-2026-prediction-437650">70%</a> of consumers say they somewhat trust generative AI search results.</h3>
<p>In contrast, a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/ai-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">recent AI statistics roundup</a> found that <a href="https://www.forbes.com/advisor/business/artificial-intelligence-consumer-sentiment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">75%</a> of consumers are concerned about misinformation from AI. However, <a href="https://dataprot.net/statistics/ai-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">50%</a> of consumers also report being optimistic about AI overall. So, it could be that while consumers are aware of the risk of misinformation of AI in general, they‚Äôre still open to using it to streamline their daily tasks, like conducting searches.</p>
<h3>14. <a href="https://searchengineland.com/search-engine-traffic-2026-prediction-437650" target="_blank" rel="noopener">79%</a> of consumers expect to use AI-enhanced search within the next year.</h3>
<p>If your customers aren‚Äôt yet taking advantage of features like AIO, expect that to change in the coming year. You can get ahead of this predicted trend by optimizing your strategy for AIOs now.</p>
<h3>15. AIOs take up <a href="https://lp.botify.com/q4.2024-aio-report" target="_blank" rel="noopener">almost half</a> of a user‚Äôs screen when searching on Google.</h3>
<p>AI Overviews take up 42% of the screen on desktop, 48% on mobile. This pushes organic results way down the page, which might be accounting for the loss in traffic many sites are reporting seeing from Google.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-example-overview-screen.webp" alt="google ai overviews - screenshare" width="806" height="373" class="aligncenter wp-image-92053 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-example-overview-screen.webp 806w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-example-overview-screen-480x222.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 806px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Depending on the device and display settings, AI Overviews can practically take up the whole screen!</em></p>
<h3>16. <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-keywords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">81%</a> of queries that get an AI Overview are done on mobile devices.</h3>
<p>About <a href="https://www.sistrix.com/blog/the-proportion-of-mobile-searches-is-more-than-you-think-what-you-need-to-know/">two-thirds</a> of all Google searches are done on mobile devices. Now, the majority of those mobile searches are getting an AIO.</p>
<h3>17. 25 to 34-year-olds on mobile devices use AI Overviews <a href="https://www.growth-memo.com/p/the-first-ever-ux-study-of-googles">the most</a>.</h3>
<p>This demographic of searchers chooses AIOs as the final answer to their queries 50% of the time.</p>
<div id="google-ai-overviews-statistics-click-impact"></div>
<h2>Do Google AI Overviews reduce clicks?</h2>
<p>Like most things in digital marketing, there is no clear yes or no answer to this question, as AIOs vary by industry. Let‚Äôs take a closer look at how AIOs are <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/14/improve-google-ads-click-through-rate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">impacting click-through rates</a>.</p>
<h3>18. AI Overviews reduce clicks by nearly <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overviews-reduce-clicks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">35%</a>.</h3>
<p>In a study of over 300,000 keywords, there was a correlation between AIO presence and a 34.5% decrease in click-through rates for top-ranking pages.</p>
<h3>19. AIOs have decreased CTRs by about <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-ctr-study-ai-overviews-rise-as-click-rates-decline/541465/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">7%</a> for top-ranking sites.</h3>
<p>Websites in the top four positions for searches using terms like what, when, where, and how saw over a 7% decrease in clickthrough rates.</p>
<h3>20. Some sites have seen a <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/seo-is-still-your-best-marketing-channel/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">20-40%</a> decrease in search traffic since the introduction of AI Overviews.</h3>
<p>Many business owners and marketers have reported seeing declines in their site traffic in light of AIOs. In the example below, one SEO expert found their traffic to be down 41% in 2024.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-statistics-seo.webp" alt="google ai overviews statistics - linkedin post regading search traffic" width="685" height="385" class="aligncenter wp-image-92054 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-statistics-seo.webp 685w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-statistics-seo-480x270.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 685px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/wilreynolds_gartner-said25-of-search-traffic-would-activity-7244078993241444352-nKEg?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop&amp;rcm=ACoAAB-ca78B25iHsjZ3_182VZCylMwB9QWNnaA" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h3>21. It‚Äôs predicted that organic click-through rates will decrease by <a href="https://www.gartner.com/en/newsroom/press-releases/2024-02-19-gartner-predicts-search-engine-volume-will-drop-25-percent-by-2026-due-to-ai-chatbots-and-other-virtual-agents">25%</a> by 2026 because of AI Overviews.</h3>
<p>However, when a branded result shows in an AIO, CTR for that brand actually <a href="https://searchengineland.com/google-organic-paid-ctr-down-451619?mkt_tok=NzI3LVpRRS0wNDQAAAGYea1pFYXNFDp86RyrRIT3ERtGGTUbJIIzq_ZkzCb9s3O0yeLdwef6BUlNM8HsHfq1ajTfoa__H1ukfbrfxqvKs4MEShz7-I1N0K4fSI07vS3u8Q" target="_blank" rel="noopener">increases</a>.</p>
<h3>22. Overall, SERPs containing AI Overviews show <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-keywords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">96% fewer</a> sitelinks, 84% fewer videos, and 75% fewer Knowledge Panels.</h3>
<p>They also trigger less thumbnails and Top Stories features.</p>
<h3>23. <a href="https://sparktoro.com/blog/2024-zero-click-search-study-for-every-1000-us-google-searches-only-374-clicks-go-to-the-open-web-in-the-eu-its-360/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">58%</a> of Google searches now result in zero clicks.</h3>
<p>This indicates that AI Overviews could be causing users to not click off from the SERP.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-search-experience.webp" alt="google ads ai overviews - searches resulting in no clicks" width="935" height="446" class="aligncenter wp-image-92049 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-search-experience.webp 935w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-search-experience-480x229.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 935px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://sparktoro.com/blog/2024-zero-click-search-study-for-every-1000-us-google-searches-only-374-clicks-go-to-the-open-web-in-the-eu-its-360/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Data source</a></em></p>
<h3>24. <a href="https://aioseo.com/seo-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">63%</a> of businesses reported that Google AI Overviews have positively impacted organic traffic, visibility, or rankings since its rollout in May 2024.</h3>
<p>On a more positive note, business owners are now <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-overviews-optimization" target="_blank" rel="noopener">embracing AIOs</a> as valuable ranking opportunities in 2025.</p>
<h3>25. AI Overview SERPs have resulted in <a href="https://www.seerinteractive.com/insights/ctr-aio">lower CTRs overall</a> compared to SERPs without AIOs for both organic and paid results.</h3>
<p>A recent study looked at data from throughout the past year and found that both paid and organic CTRs trend down when AIOs have been shown.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-ctr-chart.webp" alt="google ai overviews - chart of ctrs from ai overview pages" width="935" height="444" class="aligncenter wp-image-92051 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-ctr-chart.webp 935w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-ctr-chart-480x228.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 935px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.seerinteractive.com/insights/ctr-aio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Data source</a></em></p>
<div id="google-ai-overviews-statistics-more-stats"></div>
<h2>Even more Google AIO statistics and fun facts</h2>
<p>Want even more Google AIO statistics? I‚Äôve got you covered!</p>
<h3><span>26. Keywords with an average CPC between </span><a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-links-to-itself-43-of-ai-overviews-point-back-to-google/546574/"><span>$2-$5</span></a><span> trigger AIOs the most. </span></h3>
<p>AIOs appeared 32% of the time for keywords within this CPC price range. Meanwhile, more expensive keywords costing $10 or more only saw AIOs about 17% of the time.</p>
<p><strong>See how much keywords might cost in your industry </strong>using our free <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/google-ads-industry-benchmarks?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025GoogleAdsBenchmarks_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2025 search benchmarks report</a>!</p>
<h3>27. Queries containing technical terminology, jargon, or industry-specific, complex terms are <a href="https://searchengineland.com/google-ai-overviews-search-clicks-fell-report-455498" target="_blank" rel="noopener">48%</a> more likely to get an AI Overview.</h3>
<p>This likely also means that many long-tailed keywords, which are frequently favored by marketers and advertisers since they tend to have higher search intent, have an increased AIO presence in their results.</p>
<h3>28. Ecommerce queries <a href="https://searchengineland.com/google-ai-overviews-search-clicks-fell-report-455498" target="_blank" rel="noopener">rarely</a> get AI Overviews.</h3>
<p>In fact, the presence of AIOs in ecommerce queries has declined‚Äîwith only 4% of ecommerce searches getting AIOs, compared to 29% when AIOs first rolled out.</p>
<h3>29. The industry that saw the <a href="https://searchengineland.com/google-ai-overviews-search-clicks-fell-report-455498" target="_blank" rel="noopener">biggest increase</a> in AIO presence on SERPs this past year was B2B technology.</h3>
<p>The presence of AIOs for B2B tech-related queries increased from 36% to now 70% of SERPs containing AIOs. This is followed by Insurance (17% to 63%) and Entertainment (2% to 37%).</p>
<h3>30. <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-growth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">5.5%</a> of AI Overviews include information from Reddit.</h3>
<p>This makes Reddit the most popular site sourced in AI Overviews, followed by Quora (4% AIO share), NIH.gov (1.8% AIO share), and WebMD (1.5% AIO share).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-top-sites.webp" alt="google ai overviews - top sites chart" width="653" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92052 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-top-sites.webp 653w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-ai-overviews-top-sites-480x441.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 653px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-growth/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h3>31. The typical keyword that triggers an AI Overview has a <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-overview-keywords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">difficulty of 12 and a volume of 500</a>.</h3>
<p>Using keyword tools to familiarize yourself with your industry‚Äôs typical keyword volume and difficulty ratings can help you gauge how frequently AIOs might show up in searches relating to your business.</p>
<h3>32. Longer AI Overviews contain more sources overall.</h3>
<p>The longer an AI Overview‚Äôs answer, the more sources it cites. AIOs under 600 characters <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-links-to-itself-43-of-ai-overviews-point-back-to-google/546574/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cite about five sources</a>, while those over 6,600 characters cite around 28 sources.</p>
<h3>33. AI Overviews uses the <a href="https://searchengineland.com/how-to-get-cited-by-ai-seo-insights-from-8000-ai-citations-455284">widest range</a> of sources among all AI-powered search engines.</h3>
<p>While there are other <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/chatgpt-search" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI-supported search solutions emerging</a>, Google‚Äôs AI Overviews currently has the biggest variety in the sources that it pulls.</p>
<h3>34. In May 2025, Google expanded AI Overviews to cover users in <a href="https://blog.google/products/search/ai-overview-expansion-may-2025-update/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">200</a> different countries and 40 languages.</h3>
<p>AIO support was added for users who speak Arabic, Chinese, Malay, Urdu and more.</p>
